---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Eidos AGI — Software for agents. Governance for reality."
  description="Open-source infrastructure that makes existing AI go further. 9 packages on PyPI, all MIT."
>

  <div class="page">

    <!-- ═══ MARK ═══ -->
    <div class="mark">
      <a href="/">eidos agi</a>
      <div class="mark-right">
        <div class="theme-switcher">
          <button class="theme-dot" data-set-theme="workshop" style="background:#c4935a" title="Workshop"></button>
          <button class="theme-dot" data-set-theme="midnight" style="background:#6c8aff" title="Midnight"></button>
          <button class="theme-dot" data-set-theme="forest" style="background:#4ade80" title="Forest"></button>
          <button class="theme-dot" data-set-theme="copper" style="background:#e88a48" title="Copper"></button>
          <button class="theme-dot" data-set-theme="paper" style="background:#f0ebe4;border:1px solid #8a8078" title="Paper"></button>
          <button class="theme-dot" data-set-theme="slate" style="background:#a78bfa" title="Slate"></button>
          <button class="theme-dot theme-ai" data-set-theme="ai" title="AI Reader Mode">AI</button>
        </div>
        <nav id="nav-menu">
          <a href="https://github.com/eidos-agi">github</a>
          <a href="https://pypi.org/user/eidos-agi/">pypi</a>
        </nav>
        <button class="hamburger" id="hamburger" aria-label="Menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="nav-menu">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <line x1="3" y1="5" x2="17" y2="5"/>
            <line x1="3" y1="10" x2="17" y2="10"/>
            <line x1="3" y1="15" x2="17" y2="15"/>
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feedback drawer removed — ADR-001 (eidosagi.com): no thumbs-up/down UI, creates heft -->

    <!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-text">
        <h1>Software<br />for agents.</h1>
        <div class="hero-rule"></div>
        <h1 class="hero-muted">Governance<br />for reality.</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-viz">
        <svg class="flow-svg" viewBox="0 0 280 320" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="The Eidos trilogy flow: visionlog (governance) feeds research.md (decisions) feeds ike.md (execution), with governance contracts governing the entire loop">
          <rect class="flow-node fn-1" x="60" y="10" width="160" height="52" rx="3" />
          <text class="flow-label" x="140" y="42" text-anchor="middle">visionlog</text>
          <text class="flow-sublabel" x="140" y="28" text-anchor="middle">GOVERNANCE</text>
          <rect class="flow-node fn-2" x="60" y="120" width="160" height="52" rx="3" />
          <text class="flow-label" x="140" y="152" text-anchor="middle">research.md</text>
          <text class="flow-sublabel" x="140" y="138" text-anchor="middle">DECISIONS</text>
          <rect class="flow-node fn-3" x="60" y="230" width="160" height="52" rx="3" />
          <text class="flow-label" x="140" y="262" text-anchor="middle">ike.md</text>
          <text class="flow-sublabel" x="140" y="248" text-anchor="middle">EXECUTION</text>
          <line class="flow-arrow" x1="140" y1="62" x2="140" y2="120" />
          <polygon class="flow-head" points="134,114 140,124 146,114" />
          <line class="flow-arrow" x1="140" y1="172" x2="140" y2="230" />
          <polygon class="flow-head" points="134,224 140,234 146,224" />
          <path class="flow-feedback" d="M220 256 Q260 256 260 200 Q260 140 260 80 Q260 36 220 36" />
          <text class="flow-side-r" x="268" y="150" text-anchor="start" font-size="7" transform="rotate(90 268 150)">contracts govern</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- ═══ THE TRILOGY — immediately after hero ═══ -->
    <section class="trilogy reveal">
      <div class="trilogy-header">
        <h2>The Trilogy</h2>
        <p>Agents need governance before they act, evidence before they decide, and tracking after they execute. Three tools enforce that contract.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="trilogy-cards">
        <article class="tri">
          <span class="tri-num">I</span>
          <h3>Governance</h3>
          <p><strong>visionlog</strong> — Vision, goals, guardrails, and ADRs. The contracts all execution must honor. If a task would violate a guardrail, the answer is already no.</p>
          <code>pip install visionlog-md</code>
          <!-- Mini-viz: guardrail bar chart -->
          <div class="tri-viz">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 140 50" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Guardrail coverage bars showing compliance levels">
              <rect x="0" y="5" width="100" height="8" rx="2" fill="var(--color-primary)" opacity="0.2"/>
              <rect x="0" y="5" width="72" height="8" rx="2" fill="var(--color-primary)" opacity="0.6"/>
              <rect x="0" y="20" width="100" height="8" rx="2" fill="var(--color-secondary)" opacity="0.2"/>
              <rect x="0" y="20" width="90" height="8" rx="2" fill="var(--color-secondary)" opacity="0.6"/>
              <rect x="0" y="35" width="100" height="8" rx="2" fill="var(--color-command)" opacity="0.2"/>
              <rect x="0" y="35" width="45" height="8" rx="2" fill="var(--color-command)" opacity="0.6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="tri">
          <span class="tri-num">II</span>
          <h3>Decisions</h3>
          <p><strong>research.md</strong> — Evidence-graded, phase-gated, peer-reviewed. Decisions earned with data, not assumed in conversation.</p>
          <code>pip install research-md</code>
          <div class="tri-viz">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 140 50" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Decision funnel: many candidates narrowed to one winner">
              <path d="M10 5 L130 5 L100 25 L40 25 Z" fill="var(--color-primary)" opacity="0.12"/>
              <path d="M40 27 L100 27 L85 45 L55 45 Z" fill="var(--color-primary)" opacity="0.25"/>
              <circle cx="70" cy="48" r="3" fill="var(--color-primary)" opacity="0.6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="tri">
          <span class="tri-num">III</span>
          <h3>Execution</h3>
          <p><strong>ike.md</strong> — Tasks, milestones, Definition of Done. Named for Eisenhower.</p>
          <code>pip install ike-md</code>
          <div class="tri-viz">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 140 50" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Task checklist: two completed, one in progress, one pending">
              <rect x="0" y="5" width="10" height="10" rx="2" stroke="var(--color-command)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
              <polyline points="2,10 5,13 10,7" stroke="var(--color-command)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
              <line x1="16" y1="10" x2="90" y2="10" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="0.5"/>
              <rect x="0" y="20" width="10" height="10" rx="2" stroke="var(--color-command)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
              <polyline points="2,25 5,28 10,22" stroke="var(--color-command)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
              <line x1="16" y1="25" x2="70" y2="25" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="0.5"/>
              <rect x="0" y="35" width="10" height="10" rx="2" stroke="var(--color-primary)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
              <line x1="16" y1="40" x2="110" y2="40" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.4"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ TRILOGY MATRIX ═══ -->
    <div class="matrix reveal">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th></th>
            <th>visionlog</th>
            <th>research.md</th>
            <th>ike.md</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="matrix-label">Governs</td>
            <td>What the project committed to</td>
            <td>How decisions get earned</td>
            <td>What work gets done</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="matrix-label">When</td>
            <td>Before any work starts</td>
            <td>Before a consequential choice</td>
            <td>During execution</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="matrix-label">Outputs</td>
            <td>Vision, goals, guardrails, ADRs</td>
            <td>Scored candidates, decision brief</td>
            <td>Tasks, milestones, completion notes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="matrix-label">Install</td>
            <td><code>pip install visionlog-md</code></td>
            <td><code>pip install research-md</code></td>
            <td><code>pip install ike-md</code></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ THE REST ═══ -->
    <section class="tools reveal">
      <h2>More tools</h2>
      <div class="tools-grid">
        <a href="/tools/railguey" class="tool-card">
          <span class="tc-role">MCP</span>
          <h3>railguey</h3>
          <p>Railway deploys from Claude Code.</p>
          <code>pip install railguey</code>
        </a>
        <a href="/tools/clawdflare" class="tool-card">
          <span class="tc-role">MCP</span>
          <h3>clawdflare</h3>
          <p>Cloudflare zone auditing.</p>
          <code>pip install clawdflare</code>
        </a>
        <a href="/tools/eidos-mcp-registry" class="tool-card">
          <span class="tc-role">MCP</span>
          <h3>eidos-mcp-registry</h3>
          <p>Right tools, right project.</p>
          <code>pip install eidos-mcp-registry</code>
        </a>
        <a href="/tools/resume-resume" class="tool-card">
          <span class="tc-role">Agent</span>
          <h3>resume-resume</h3>
          <p>Post-crash session recovery.</p>
          <code>pip install resume-resume</code>
        </a>
        <a href="/tools/apple-a-day" class="tool-card">
          <span class="tc-role">Agent</span>
          <h3>apple-a-day</h3>
          <p>Mac health. Zero deps.</p>
          <code>pip install apple-a-day</code>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ WHY — philosophy comes after the tools ═══ -->
    <section class="about reveal">
      <div class="about-lead">
        <p>Amazon didn't create the internet. It created the trust infrastructure — reviews, ratings, guaranteed delivery — that made people willing to buy from strangers online. We're doing the same thing for AI agents.</p>
        <p class="about-punch">We don't build LLMs. We build the governance, decisions, and execution standards that make them trustworthy enough to hand real work.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="about-aside">
        <div class="aside-stat">9 <span>packages on PyPI</span></div>
        <div class="aside-stat">MIT <span>licensed, all of them</span></div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="trust reveal">
      <h2>Built in the open</h2>
      <div class="trust-body">
        <p>If the tools that govern your agents are closed, you're trusting the vendor. If they're open, you're trusting the code. We think that's a better deal. The core is MIT-licensed and always will be.</p>
        <p>We build enterprise products too — governance at scale, compliance, SLAs. But the foundation is public and auditable. Trust us because you read the source, not because we asked nicely.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <blockquote class="urgency reveal">
      <p>Agents are getting deployed into real systems right now — if you don't give them governed tools, explicit decisions, and agent-grade interfaces, you're shipping a probabilistic coworker with production access.</p>
    </blockquote>

    <!-- ═══ ENTERPRISE ═══ -->
    <section class="enterprise reveal">
      <div class="ent-grid">
        <div class="ent-text">
          <h2>Enterprise</h2>
          <p>The open-source tools handle governance for individual teams. When you need it across an organization — multi-team policy enforcement, compliance reporting, audit trails, SSO — that's what the enterprise layer does.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Centralized guardrail management across teams</li>
            <li>Compliance reporting and audit exports</li>
            <li>SSO and role-based access control</li>
            <li>Priority support and SLAs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="ent-cta">
          <p class="ent-note">Same tools. Same codebase. More surface area.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/eidos-agi" class="contribute-btn">Talk to us on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ CONTRIBUTE ═══ -->
    <section class="contribute reveal">
      <h2>Contribute</h2>
      <p>Everything is open source. Everything is MIT. If you see the gap — reach out.</p>
      <div class="contribute-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/eidos-agi" class="contribute-btn">Browse the repos</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="foot">
      <span>&copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} Eidos AGI</span>
    </footer>

  </div>

<script>
  // ── Theme switcher ──
  const saved = localStorage.getItem('eidos-theme');
  if (saved && saved !== 'workshop') document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', saved);

  document.querySelectorAll('[data-set-theme]').forEach(btn => {
    if (btn.dataset.setTheme === (saved || 'workshop')) btn.classList.add('active');
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const theme = btn.dataset.setTheme;
      if (theme === 'workshop') {
        document.documentElement.removeAttribute('data-theme');
      } else {
        document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', theme);
      }
      localStorage.setItem('eidos-theme', theme);
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-set-theme]').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
      btn.classList.add('active');
    });
  });

  // ── Feedback drawer ──
  // Hamburger menu
  const hamburgerBtn = document.getElementById('hamburger');
  const navMenu = document.getElementById('nav-menu');
  if (hamburgerBtn && navMenu) {
    hamburgerBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      navMenu.classList.toggle('open');
      hamburgerBtn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', navMenu.classList.contains('open'));
    });
    document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      if (!hamburgerBtn.contains(e.target) && !navMenu.contains(e.target)) {
        navMenu.classList.remove('open');
      }
    });
  }
</script>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .page {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  /* ── MARK ── */
  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: var(--space-16);
    align-items: center;
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-12);
    min-height: auto;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7vw, 5.5rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
  }
  .hero-rule {
    width: 64px;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
  }
  .hero-muted { color: var(--color-muted); }

  /* Flow diagram */
  .flow-svg { width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .flow-node {
    fill: var(--color-surface);
    stroke: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 30%, transparent);
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .fn-1 { stroke: var(--color-primary); }
  .fn-2 { stroke: var(--color-primary); opacity: 0.7; }
  .fn-3 { stroke: var(--color-primary); opacity: 0.5; }
  .flow-label {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 14px;
    fill: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .flow-sublabel {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 8px;
    fill: var(--color-primary);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
  .flow-arrow {
    stroke: var(--color-primary);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    stroke-dasharray: 4 3;
  }
  .flow-head { fill: var(--color-primary); }
  .flow-side-r {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    fill: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .flow-feedback {
    stroke: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 30%, transparent);
    stroke-width: 1;
    stroke-dasharray: 3 4;
    fill: none;
  }
  @keyframes dash { to { stroke-dashoffset: -14; } }
  .flow-arrow { animation: dash 1.5s linear infinite; }
  .flow-feedback { animation: dash 3s linear infinite reverse; }

  /* ── ABOUT ── */
  .about {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    padding: var(--space-16) 0;
    border-top: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .about-lead p {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    max-width: var(--measure-prose);
  }
  .about-punch {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    color: var(--color-text);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .about-aside {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    padding-left: var(--space-8);
    border-left: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
  }
  .aside-stat {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .aside-stat span {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: var(--weight-regular);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
  }

  /* ── TRUST ── */
  .trust {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0;
    border-top: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
  }
  .trust h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  .trust-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-8);
  }
  .trust-body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  /* ── URGENCY ── */
  .urgency {
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-8);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-12);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-danger);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-danger) 5%, transparent);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }
  .urgency p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    max-width: var(--measure-prose);
    color: var(--color-danger);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── TRILOGY ── */
  .trilogy {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0;
    border-top: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
  }
  .trilogy-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .trilogy-header h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .trilogy-header p { color: var(--color-muted); }
  .trilogy-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  .tri {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .tri-num {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .tri h3 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
  }
  .tri p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .tri p strong { color: var(--color-text); font-weight: var(--weight-medium); }
  .tri code { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-command); }
  .tri-viz {
    margin-top: auto;
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  .tri-viz svg { width: 100%; height: auto; opacity: 0.7; }

  /* ── TRILOGY MATRIX ── */
  .matrix {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-12);
  }
  .matrix table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }
  .matrix thead th {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
  }
  .matrix thead th:first-child { color: var(--color-muted); }
  .matrix tbody td {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 10%, transparent);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }
  .matrix-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .matrix code {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-command);
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .matrix { overflow-x: auto; }
    .matrix table { min-width: 600px; }
  }

  /* ── TOOLS GRID ── */
  .tools {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0;
    border-top: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
  }
  .tools h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .tools-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }
  .tool-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-4);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    transition: transform 200ms ease;
  }
  .tool-card:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .tc-role {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .tool-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: var(--weight-medium);
    color: var(--color-text);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
